{"id":"nucl-th/9904074","submitter":"Chi-Keung Chow","authors":"Chi-Keung Chow, Thomas D. Cohen","title":"Enhanced Signatures for Disoriented Chiral Condensates","comments":"8 pages in REVTeX, 5 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":"DOE/ER/40762-180, UMD PP#99-106","categories":"nucl-th hep-ph nucl-ex","license":null,"abstract":"  The probability distribution in $R$, the proportion of neutral pions to all\npions emitted in heavy ion collisions in certain kinematic regions, has been\nsuggested as a signal of a disoriented chiral condensate (D$\\chi$C). Here we\nnote that the signature can be greatly enhanced by making suitable cuts in the\ndata. In particular, we consider reducing the data set such that the $k$ pions\nwith lowest $p_T$ are all neutral. We find that, given such cuts, $<R >$ can be\nsubstantially different from 1/3. For example, for a single D$\\chi$C domain\nwithout contamination due to incoherently emitted pions, $<R>$ is 3/5 given the\npion with lowest $p_T$ is neutral, and 5/7 given the two pions with lowest\n$p_T$ are both neutral, etc.. The effects of multi-domain D$\\chi$C formation\nand noise due to incoherent pion emission can be systematically incorporated.\nPotential applications to experiments and their limitations are briefly\ndiscussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Apr 1999 20:52:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
